=Description=

"A self-organizing work group (SOWG) is a collection of people stepping outside of their formal organizational structure to collectively take responsibility for a complete work process or project. Within the group, roles and jobs are defined and redefined as needed by group members so they can work in more interchangeable ways and so that the group can function in more flexible, organic ways (adapted from Morgan, 1997). These groups appear to come into being without much planning and to emerge from local interactions among people pursuing their individual agendas."
